<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1295,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,1295,1321]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[313,377,1296,1322]" name="Japan" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Honshu, Kyushu) (
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[609,955,1295,1322]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda 1996: 162</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. &amp; Su, C. - Y. &amp; Zhu, D. - H." box="[968,1208,1295,1322]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="807 - 824" refId="ref44701" refString="Ide, T., Abe, Y., Su, C. - Y. &amp; Zhu, D. - H. (2018 a) Three species of Andricus Hartig (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) inducing similar galls in East Asia, with description of a new species and the asexual generation of A. pseudocurvator, and redescription of A. moriokae. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 120 (4), 807 - 824. https: // doi. org / 10.4289 / 0013 - 8797.120.4.807" type="journal article" year="2018">
Ide 
<emphasis box="[1012,1063,1295,1321]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2018a: 821
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1230,1298,1296,1322]" name="South Korea" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda 1996: 162</bibRefCitation>
), and the Russian Far East (
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[697,905,1331,1358]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="15 - 21" refId="ref48520" refString="Monzen, K. (1953) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (I). Cynipidae (Cynipinae), Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of the Gakugei Faculty of the Iwate University, 5, 15 - 21." type="journal article" year="1953">Monzen 1953: 19</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovalev, O. V." box="[920,1129,1331,1358]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="25 - 38" refId="ref45839" refString="Kovalev, O. V. (1965) Gall wasps (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae) from the south of the Soviet Far East. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 44 (1 / 2), 46 - 73. [in Russian; English translation in Entomology Review, 44, 25 - 38]" type="journal article" year="1965">Kovalev 1965: 35</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda 1996: 162</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1295,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1404,1430]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
The alternating lifecycle was closed and the asexual generation was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Katsuda, T. &amp; Yukawa, J." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="111 - 123" refId="ref45595" refString="Katsuda, T. &amp; Yukawa, J. (2004) Gall wasps (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) in Kyushu, Japan. Esakia, 44, 111 - 123. https: // doi. org / 10.5109 / 2687" type="journal article" year="2004">Katsuda &amp; Yukawa (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. &amp; Su, C. - Y. &amp; Zhu, D. - H." box="[355,547,1439,1466]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="807 - 824" refId="ref44701" refString="Ide, T., Abe, Y., Su, C. - Y. &amp; Zhu, D. - H. (2018 a) Three species of Andricus Hartig (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) inducing similar galls in East Asia, with description of a new species and the asexual generation of A. pseudocurvator, and redescription of A. moriokae. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 120 (4), 807 - 824. https: // doi. org / 10.4289 / 0013 - 8797.120.4.807" type="journal article" year="2018">
Ide 
<emphasis box="[397,446,1439,1465]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. (2018a)
</bibRefCitation>
reported that the asexual form mentioned by these authors for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monzen" authorityYear="1953" box="[1248,1385,1439,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moriokae">
<emphasis box="[1248,1385,1439,1466]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A. moriokae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
corresponds, in fact, to the asexual generation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Tang &amp; Melika, 2011" authorityName="Tang &amp; Melika" authorityYear="2011" box="[666,1122,1475,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudocurvator">
<emphasis box="[666,873,1475,1502]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A. pseudocurvator</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Nicholls, J. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N." box="[879,1122,1475,1502]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="725180" refId="ref48131" refString="Melika, G., Tang, C. - T., Nicholls, J., Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2011) Four new species of Dryocosmus gallwasps from Taiwan (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae, Cynipini). ISRN Zoology, 2011, 725180. https: // doi. org / 10.5402 / 2011 / 725180" type="journal article" year="2011">Tang &amp; Melika, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1295,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1511,1537]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Biology.</emphasis>
The sexual generation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monzen" authorityYear="1953" box="[590,728,1511,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moriokae">
<emphasis box="[590,728,1511,1538]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A. moriokae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
develops in integral leaf galls on 
<taxonomicName box="[1112,1231,1511,1538]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dentata">
<emphasis box="[1112,1231,1511,1538]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Q. dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1287,1403,1512,1538]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[1287,1403,1512,1538]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Q. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName box="[151,323,1547,1574]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandulifera">
<emphasis box="[151,323,1547,1574]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Q. glandulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[407,501,1548,1574]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[407,501,1548,1574]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[624,782,1547,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="15 - 21" refId="ref48520" refString="Monzen, K. (1953) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (I). Cynipidae (Cynipinae), Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of the Gakugei Faculty of the Iwate University, 5, 15 - 21." type="journal article" year="1953">Monzen 1953</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovalev, O. V." box="[794,954,1547,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="25 - 38" refId="ref45839" refString="Kovalev, O. V. (1965) Gall wasps (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae) from the south of the Soviet Far East. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 44 (1 / 2), 46 - 73. [in Russian; English translation in Entomology Review, 44, 25 - 38]" type="journal article" year="1965">Kovalev 1965</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[965,1247,1547,1574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
